Package edu.cpp.cs.cs241.project3

Class Project3

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.cpp.cs.cs241.project3.Project3
  • public class Project3
extends java.lang.Object
    This class implements the program. The program reads data from two files: "city.dat" and "road.dat", in order to demonstrate our implementation of a graph and specifically getting a shortest path in the graph using Dijkstra's algorithm. The program essentially provides the user an interface in which they can query info about a city, find the shortest path between two cities, insert a new road between two cities and remove a road between two cities.

    "city.dat" format: for each line in the file, [number code name population elevation] with types respective to a City object.

    "road.dat" format: for each line in the file, [sourceVertex targetVertex weight] all integers, with the vertices being its number in the graph, for example sourceVertex 1 is the first vertex in the graph, 2 for second and so on.
